insights.title: High TCP Retransmission Rate on 192.168.146.97
insights.description: A high number of TCP packets originating from 192.168.146.97:8883 are being retransmitted, indicating potential network congestion or reliability issues.  The 54 byte tcp packets are almost exclusively the packets which are retransmitted.
insights.impact: Performance degradation for MQTT clients connected to this broker (likely 192.168.146.97)

insights.title: External MQTT Communication Delays
insights.description: Large delays observed in MQTT communications towards external IP addresses (54.165.29.152:443), indicating a potential bottleneck or increased latency in external network paths.
insights.impact: Affects all mqtt message traffic towards external networks

insights.title: Excessive TCP retransmissions causing latency
insights.description: The overwhelming number of TCP retransmissions (Flags: retransmission: true) contribute to considerable latency in end-to-end MQTT communications.
insights.impact: Affects all mqtt message traffic on 192.168.146.97 subnet

correlations.title: Packet Size and Retransmission
correlations.description: The retransmission primarily affects TCP packets with size 54, which is almost exclusively the retransmitted packets, highlighting an issue with the default TCP ACK packet.

correlations.title: Internal vs External Traffic
correlations.description: MQTT traffic to external addresses (AWS, and other external endpoints) causes a spike in retransmissions as opposed to traffic within the local network.
